    <p>IoT sensors lay the foundation for a bigger connected system for monitoring weather conditions. These systems rely on a network of connected sensors that collect data in the field. Cloud computing platforms then process the collected data to provide alarms and notifications on potential weather hazards affecting crops.</p>

