    <p>Agribusinesses are also using satellites for weather forecasting to monitor global climate changes and predict weather disasters like fires and floods. Most often, satellites are controlled by government organizations and therefore arenâ€™t flexible enough for custom use cases. Still, they provide the overall picture of weather conditions in an area. Collecting satellite images and data empowers AgriTech applications to assist in predicting crop yields based on weather conditions and field monitoring. It also helps in planning smart irrigation based on weather changes that can spread potentially dangerous herbicides across the terrain.</p>
